Changelog.Description: Updated endpoint to properly exclude non-equipment assets.
Changelog.Details: The endpoint originally did not properly filter for the asset being a piece of equipment, leading to the endpoint being usable but not supported for non-equipment assets. We now have other endpoints that cover the other primary asset types and can be used instead.

Changelog.Description: Updates endpoint to include new gatewayJ1939EngineSeconds stat type.
Changelog.Details: Adds gatewayJ1939EngineSeconds to surface manual engine second readings when using a J1939/CAT cable that supports obd readings. This allows customers to fetch engine seconds that match engine hour readings on cloud.samsara.com.

Changelog.Description: Updates endpoint to support gateway replace.
Changelog.Details: Adds a gatewaySerial field to allow customers to replace the connected gateway to their vehicle. Gateway needs to be activated on the same organization already. Deactivates the gateway previously linked.

Changelog.Description: Update returned gateway accessory devices and gateway model types.
Changelog.Details: The previous version returned accessory devices with name, serial, firmware, and last connected time. This version returns the connected camera and/or sensors and their respective serials and model names.

Changelog.Description: Updated endpoint to use the time a vehicle assignment ended as the time for signout events to accurately reflect the driver's signout time.
Changelog.Details: For signout events, HOS Audit logs retrieved will now return the time of signout for the logStartMs field rather than returning the time the vehicle assignment began.

Changelog.Description: This endpoint now returns shipping and trailer IDs as strings instead of ints. + This endpoint now accepts GET requests instead of POST requests.
Changelog.Details: Shipping and trailer IDs were previously returned as ints. As a result, shipping and trailer IDs containing non-numerical characters showed up blank in responses.Shipping and trailer IDs are now returned as strings, allowing non-numerical characters.

The api endpoint now leverages pagination on drivers for a more performant call.

Adds a pagination dictionary to the response body with endCursor and hasNextPage parameters, and removes the group ID request args requirement. The actual fleet locations response remains unchanged from past versions. Also adds optional tag IDs and vehicle IDs filters.
Creation of driver messages will no longer accept messages with a length greater than 2500 characters.

Changelog.Description: Updated endpoint to report composite unassigned driving segments if applicable when querying for an unassigned driving segment by id.
Changelog.Details: Endpoint can now return a new status called 'MULTIPLE', which indicates that the unassigned driving segment has multiple composite segments; composite segments will be returned nested under a new field called 'segments'. Unassigned driving segments will now also return a string representing duty status.
